baseline.comment:
1. Number of women at decision making positions: 
a) Parliament - 6%; b) Government - 21 %; c) Local Self-Government - 11%;

2. a. While the women's unemployment rate (14.5%) is lower than that of the men (17.9%), there is a gap between the women and men earnings; 
b. gender pay gap - 57 tetri for women and vs. 1 Gel for men  (2010)

